<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-24T15:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-24T15:44:00-05:00" n="651" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/438</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-24T17:00:00-03:44">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Charter contract for ex-German vessels signed this afternoon will be
                                handed to Congress today. Minister of Foreign Affairs expects that
                                it will pass Senate Wednesday, from there must go to House of
                                    Representatives.<note n="2" xml:id="d651fn2">The signature, on
                                    June 3, of the Executive decree promulgating the legislative
                                    approval of the contract was reported by the Chargé in telegram
                                    of June 12, 11 p.m. (File No. 862.85/468.)</note> Referring to
                                article 10 of contract, what arrangements have been made as to
                                payment of the advance on charter price for repairs?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>